{"title_page": "Mercedes-Benz Travego", "text_new": "{{Infobox UK Bus\n|background       =\n|name             = Mercedes-Benz Travego\n|image            = File:Mercedes Travego, Vagebund.JPG\n|imagesize        = \n|caption          = Travego M 2nd generation facelift\n|manufacturer     = [[Mercedes-Benz buses|Mercedes-Benz]]\n|production       = since 1999\n|predecessor      = \n|successor        = \n|class            = \n|capacity         =\n|operator         =\n|length           =\n|width            =\n|height           =\n|floortype        = High floor\n|doors            = 2\n|weight           =\n|chassis          =\n|engine           =\n|powerout         ={{convert|315|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}}\n|transmission     =Mercedes-Benz 6-speed, GO 210, servo-assisted }}\nThe '''Mercedes-Benz Travego''' (also known as O580) is an integral [[coach (bus)|coach]] produced between 1999 and 2017 by [[Daimler AG|Daimler]]/[[EvoBus]] in [[Neu-Ulm]] and [[Mannheim]] in [[Germany]] and since 2005 in [[Hosdere]] in [[Turkey]]. It was originally introduced as the flagship of [[Mercedes-Benz]] touring coach range.<ref>{{cite web|title=Czas na dentobusy! Jakie Mercedesy zabuduje Zeszuta?|url=http://infobus.pl/czas-na-dentobusy-jakie-mercedesy-zabuduje-zeszuta-_more_100517.html|agency=infobus.pl|accessdate=2017-12-03|language=pl}}</ref>\n\n==First generation==\n\n==Second generation==\n\n==Third generation==\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Travego, Istanbul (LRM 20191212 155441).jpg|Travego SHD 3rd generation\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n\n{{Mercedes-Benz}}\n\n[[Category:Mercedes-Benz buses|Travego]]\n[[Category:Vehicles introduced in 1999]]\n[[Category:Coaches (bus)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox UK Bus\n|background       =\n|name             = Mercedes-Benz Travego\n|image            = File:Mercedes Travego, Vagebund.JPG\n|imagesize        = \n|caption          = Travego M 2nd generation facelift\n|manufacturer   